	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65539270"><p>When I left Britain quarter of a decade ago, yes, very few had air conditioning, and I suspect that's still the case. Air conditioning is expensive, and people are far more frugal in Europe than in the US.</p><p>I'm wondering though if the rise in popularity of heat pumps might introduce Europeans to air conditioning indirectly. Given they're supposedly far more efficient than regular electric heaters, which people do buy (because they're cheap!), it seems like a win against heat stroke deaths which are alas common over there.</p></div>
	</div>

