		<div id="comment_body_65539218">Google says about 1/6th of European buildings use heat pumps for heating.  A heat pump is just an A/C unit operating backwards.  A reversible heat pump does both

With Europe's warmer climate, as well as advances in heat pump technology, it seems like heat pumps would be viable in most of Europe.

Heat pumps are more efficient and can use greener sources of energy.  As well as reduce dependence on non-EU fossil fuel sources.  All of that is a win.

It seems like the added desire, if not need, for A/C could</div>
